column5: My gawd man, can you get anymore stuff on that machine???????????????
I’m sure I can get a few more things on it. Lol
I don't see any fish in the pic? Whats up with that?? LOL  Thats a slick rig though. Very slick.  S.
FISH ? There is no fish in this lake. Someone once told me this.
Quite the machine, remember seeing the one on #11 eons ago, way up on the pole.  Read somewhere there were a couple of mishaps with ATV's going for a plop in the cracks, both got rescued.
That would be fun to tool around on.
Can I request a cappuccino machine ?
We would need a long Extension Cord
Terry, you should sell sandwiches and beer off the back of that thing
Nope, just strap a 2KW generator on there.
Guys guys, dont give him anymore ideas. LOL
I said Extension Cord  as an excuse to not bring a cappuccino machine Now i have no reason not to
You have a coffee maker already. Propane. If your not going to use it, I will. LOL
I wonder if they make a  propane cappuccino machine  lol
Cripes, I just welded up a rack extension for my bike and I was feeling pretty good about myself, that's just off the hook lol.  Nice rig!
Can we get all the stuff at Princess Auto for doing these same mods to our own bikes Terry? That thing is gnarly... but it kinda makes me giggle too.
Everything except the track
Really!?!?!  That's some awesome ingenuity.

Have you had it out in really deep snow yet, Terry? Do you strap skis on it in deep snow? Its gotta be one of the most versitile rigs I've seen for sure. And a yammy to boot....can't go wrong there  S.
Pretty sure that was Nick and I.  B just buys em from costco, hides em in his hut then before we leave shows us all  the fish he 'Caught'.
I have been in 3 for of snow with the skis no problem smaller foot print then skidoos and they are on with straps
Your garage is a mess. I could clean it out for ya ,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
You just leave  the 2 boats 4 motors   2 pontoon boats 3 trolling motors and two trailers where they are lol
Awesome. Sounds like my garage. I do a spring clean up and the wife loves me until I get all the summer gear from the back garage in there, and we are making trails thru the gear LOL. S.
